This paper is about a pre-training and fine-tuning framework for natural language generation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which specifically deals with NLP and its computational aspects. The second likely sub-category is cs.LG (Learning), as the paper discusses pre-training and fine-tuning of a language generation model. The third likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as NLP is a subfield of AI. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper discusses the use of neural networks for language generation. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as some of the tasks mentioned in the paper, such as question answering and summarization, are related to information retrieval.
